-------What is spring and Spring Boot------------------
-> Spring Boot ek framework hai jo ki java application ko build karne ke kaam aata hai.
-> Spring Boot hame tools provide karta hai jiski madat se ham Spring application bana shakte hai java me.
-> Spring Boot make it easy to create stand-alone, production-grade spring based application
that you can just run
-> Sping me hame bahut sare configiratation lhikni padti thi to wo configiratation ko kaam karne
or aasan bana ne ke liye aaya apna spring boot.
-> Spring Application ko easily create karne ke liye aaya apna spring boot.
-> The core spring framework already reduce boilerplate code and provides a lot of helpfull
features for java application
-> Spring framework bhi accha tha kyu ki boilerplate reduce kardeta tha and provide karta tha
helpfull features
-> However, Spring boot takes this convenience to the next level by focusing  specifically
on reducing the effort required to setup and configure a spring application.
-> Spring boot ne wo suvidha de di boilerplate wali and congigiration wali jisse hamara kaam
or easy ho jata hai kyu hame lhikna nhai padta.
-> While Spring does simplify many tasks like creating web application , working with database, managing transaction
and more .
-> Spring aasan bana deta tha creating web application , working with database, managing transaction or bahut kuch
->  but setting up a spring project can still involve quite a bite of mannual configuration.
-> This is where Spring Boot steps in.
-> Spring boot provide Auto-Configuration Standalone Application.
-> spring boot hame Auto-Configuration and Standalone Application bana ne ke shakti deta hai agar hame
ye Application ko deploy karna hai to hame koi tom-cat webserver alag se install karne ki jarrurat nhai hai or
nahi koi configuration lhik ne ki jarrurat hai kyuki spring boot me tom-cat webserver embedded hai matlab
phele se hi install aata hai tom-cat server jispe ham apne  jar ko direct server me daal shakte hai bina
configuration lhike hue.

-> we use the @(SpringBootApplication) annotaion on the main class. this single annotation replaces the
need for setting up mannual spring application context.
-> annaotaion ka matlab hai ki ham kuch hint de rhae hai ki wo chiz aisi hai or wo chiz waisi hai
-> we no longer need to explicitly create an application context using AnnotaionConfigApplication as spring
boot handles that behind the scenes.
-> We use SpringApplication.run() to start the application, and Spring Boot takes care of configuring the
embedded web server and other necessary components.
-> The @SpringBootApplication annotaion alone brings in a lot of pre-configured features, including
| automatic component scanning | and | embedded server configuration | which would have required  more steps
in traditional spring setup.
